## Integration with Gatsby

In case you have your website made with Gatsby, I made a Gatbsy Theme that will remove all the steps from below.

The theme is called `gatsby-theme-jsonresume`, you can find more information inside the [repository](https://github.com/EmaSuriano/gatsby-theme-jsonresume). In a nutshell, you need to add the theme to your Gatsby Config (`gatbsy-config.js`), send as a parameter the JSON of the resume, and then everytime you build your website it will generate the resume (`.pdf` and `.html`) and add them as new routes in your project.

These routes are accesible from anywhere in your application, therefore the only thing you need to do is create the entry points that will take the user to them. Example:

```javascript
// gatsby-config.js
module.exports = {
  plugins: [
    {
      resolve: `gatsby-theme-jsonresume`,
      options: {
        resumeJson: {
          /* ...JSON Resume Schema */
        },
      },
    },
  ],
};
```

```javascript
// src/index.js
import React from 'react';

const LandingPage = () => (
  <div>
    <h1>Welcome to my Wonderful Website</h1>
    <h2>
      {`Check out my Resume: ${(<a href="/resume.html">Web version</a>)} or ${(
        <a href="/resume.pdf">PDF version</a>
      )}`}
    </h2>
  </div>
);

export default LandingPage;
```

